P.S. Forgot to get all my engagement points. The tutorial is in collaboration with @thirdweb_, an all-in-one smart contract suite (nfts, memebrship pfps, daos, blockchain games, etc).
I am confident that @KennethCassel will continue to execute on this project, so if you know some web dev and want to take a plunge into web3, please check it out!

The newest tutorial just launched last week and it asks you to make an NFT loot box on Polygon. This will be an interesting challenge since I haven't interacted with it much. You can also earn a couple $MATIC to sweeten the deal. 

https://t.co/nqb9lgxQjq

I did like that the team was updating the course as people completed (common bugs were sorted out before I got to the section). Looking back, I see they even added a TOS which is awesome. It was also nice to have other Windows users in the discord to help me out. üòÖ

This tutorial took me longer than I want to admit - part being that I hadn't brushed up on my JS in a while and I didn't know how the course was laid out. I think the team can do a better job at laying out what skills you need before jumping in.

I learned that since blockchains are immutable (changes can't be overwritten), you have to move all your scripts to a new smart contract once you make a change. I saw a post by @iam_preethi that covers this idea in more detail.

https://t.co/MRX2POj7mF

In the first tutorial we made a "keyboard" shop fitted with tipping. We used hardhat to setup test accounts and run our contracts. 

I almost got giddy when I first ran this contract for my 1st keyboard. https://t.co/SBZzCGbEJZ
FCC will hold your hand if you are a total newbie. Cryptozombies introduce the syntax used in Solidity and the Ethereum ecosystem.

A few caveats: If you don't know basic Javascript or React, then I would suggest 
1. https://t.co/iTrVh59b2S (JS Algo and Data Structures + Front End Libraries)
2. https://t.co/scuImJ4cnb

Fair warning this might take a few weeks to go through. Come back to this post then.

.@pointer_gg released a web3 full stack tutorial that just might change the game. As one of the first 100 users to complete the first project, I was able to snag this cool keyboard. Future tutorials will pay you to learn (more on that later)üßµ https://t.co/xudORXlszG

@lukecannon727 This is crazy dude. Greed kinda takes over at a certain point so I'm down for the ride now.

Two coworkers made conversation about NFTs this week. I had to play dumb, but I couldn't put why into words.

Friends do the same thing with stocks: "hey how do I invest money?"
- suggests index funds / dca

1 month later:
"I bought ___, ____, and ___ and made $10 wtff" https://t.co/stUL8mOZ6r

I still largely use USD as my unit of account because I haven't "made it" and most things that I purchase don't have a crypto payment yet. I'd rather hold onto my crypto and borrow against instead of selling to pay for things. This will shift in the coming years.

With this recent downtick, you'd expect NFT prices to go "up", but some are the same in ETH terms. There are other examples like apes that are increasing in ETH but have retained their value in USD. It's weird to mentally arbitrage how you value assets.

I wonder when people officially change their unit of account from their native currency to a digital currency

Is it context-dependent (buying a house vs a pack of gum) or does it also depend on net worth?

If you're reading this, I hope you do something that you used to love to do as a kid. 

As for me, I will be solving a functional equation from SyberMath

f[ x^2 + yf(z) ] = x*f(x) + z* f(y)

My dad turned 20,000 days old a few days ago. I must have made this calendar event back in middle school. Of course, he was confused when I told him haha. 

Math has always been a source of happiness and intrinsic motivation for as long as I can remember.

The real lesson here is to use flashbots rpc for all your extremely sensitive dealings. Since it's private, other people can't frontrun you. Also OS is just bonkers for this tbh. https://t.co/G19c3oX7OB
